  "texts": [
    "If the control group is treated in consecutive periods, then the treatment eect at the second period gets dierenced out by the DID, generating negative weights that might cause the TWFE to be negative even if all ATEs are positive.",
    "We used their provided Stata package, twowayfeweights, to diagnose the presence of negative weights in our baseline TWFE regressions.",
    "These statistics are reported in Table A.7 Panel A.",
    "We can see that for almost all treated units (LATEs), the weights are positive.",
    "Next, we apply the complementary diagnostic by Jakiela (2021), focusing on the event-study sample."
  ]
